Privacy Policy for Study Planner — Smart Agenda

Last Updated: March 18, 2026

1. Introduction
Study Planner — Smart Agenda ("we," "our," or "the App") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.

2. Information We Collect
Study Planner — Smart Agenda operates entirely offline and does NOT collect, transmit, or share any personal data with third parties. All data you enter into the App — including classes, tasks, exams, grades, subjects, and study timer sessions — is stored locally on your device only.

The App does NOT collect:

Personal identification information (name, email, phone number)
Location data
Usage analytics or tracking data
Browsing history
Contacts or address book information
3. Data Storage
All user data is stored locally on your device using an encrypted local database. No data is uploaded to any server, cloud service, or external storage. Your data remains entirely on your device at all times.

4. Permissions
The App requests the following device permissions:

Notifications: To send you reminders for classes, tasks, and exams at your specified times.
Exact Alarm / Schedule Exact Alarm: To ensure reminders fire at the precise times you set.
Vibrate: To provide haptic feedback for timer alerts and notifications.
Wake Lock: To keep the study timer running accurately in the background.
Foreground Service: To maintain the study timer countdown when the App is minimized.
Boot Completed: To reschedule your reminders after your device restarts.
These permissions are used solely for the App's core functionality and not for data collection.

5. Third-Party Services
Study Planner — Smart Agenda does not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services. We do not use Google Analytics, Firebase Analytics, Facebook SDK, or any similar tracking tools.

6. Children's Privacy
Our App is suitable for users of all ages, including children under 13. Since we do not collect any personal information, the App complies with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and similar regulations worldwide.

7. Data Deletion
Since all data is stored locally on your device, you can delete all App data at any time by:

Using the "Clear All Data" option in the App's Settings screen, or
Uninstalling the App from your device.
8. Data Security
We take data security seriously. All data is stored in an encrypted local database on your device. Since no data leaves your device, there is no risk of data breaches from server-side attacks.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

